{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed system architecture and three separate modern algorithms-namely, SpaCy, CoreNLP, and NLTK-are used to test the dataset [87].",
    "FIRE 2010 datasetWith the use of the IOBES encoding scheme, 40 distinct tags were manually added to the Marathi news text corpus (FIRE 2010).",
    "The average length of 15 words and the corpus contains 27,177 sentences in Marathi.",
    "Both the system's training and testing employ the FIRE corpus, which was created using news articles.",
    "By tokenizing the news documents, a tokenizer creates word forms that are combined into a single file while maintaining all punctuation and sentence separators."
  ]
}